  "response_text": "A clean-cut adult man with short dark hair stands in front of wooden shelves filled with household cleaning bottles and rows of Easy-Off BAM tubs. He wears a light blue button-up shirt tucked into tan trousers and gestures with both hands as if presenting the product. On a white counter beside him, several purple-lidded tubs with teal labels are stacked in a pyramid, their labels showing a bright burst design and the large words “Easy-Off BAM.”\n\nThe visuals shift to examples of dirt and grease. A pale tiled bathroom floor near the base of a toilet is marked with dark, muddy footprints and scattered spots. A stovetop is shown with black burner grates, a dirty pot, and brown-black grease splatters across the white enamel surface; bold white text across the bottom reads “BURNT-ON GREASE.” Outdoors, a white slatted patio chair is covered with dust, soil, and fallen brown leaves. Large white text appears over it reading “GROUND-IN DIRT.”\n\nThe product is then featured in close-up: a purple plastic jar with a teal label reading “Power Cleaner Easy-Off BAM Power Cleaning Crystals,” surrounded by a pink and white starburst graphic. A red, three-dimensional “NEW” graphic appears beside the jar, with white rays behind it, while the product stands upright against a softly blurred kitchen-like background.\n\nBack in a bright kitchen, the same man stands behind a white countertop wearing yellow rubber cleaning gloves. Behind him are light wood cabinets, open shelves, a tiled backsplash, and a stovetop. On the counter in front of him are a clear glass bowl of water and an open tub of Easy-Off BAM. He holds his gloved hands out as he demonstrates. A close-up shows a white measuring scoop filled with powdery white crystals. The scoop tips, and the crystals pour out in a thick stream. They fall into the bowl of water next to the standing product tub, where the mixture begins to turn cloudy and foamy.\n\nThe bathroom floor with the muddy footprints returns. A flat mop with a green-and-yellow sponge head is pushed across the dirty tiles. As it passes over the marks, the dark footprints disappear, leaving the pale square tiles clean and mostly unmarked.\n\nA heavily stained, orange-brown greasy surface is shown with a line of white cleaning crystals sprinkled across it. A blue container held by a yellow-gloved hand pours water onto the crystals, creating a wet, foaming trail through the baked-on residue. The demonstration moves back to the dirty stovetop: a yellow-gloved hand wipes the white enamel surface with a folded white cloth near the burner grates and the dirty pot. As the cloth moves across the splatters, the area it covers becomes clean and glossy.\n\nThe cleaner is also used on a white bathtub or basin. A yellow-gloved hand scrubs with a blue sponge around a smooth, curved surface near a metal drain, clearing away dull grime and leaving a bright white patch. Outdoors again, the same yellow-gloved hand scrubs the slatted white patio chair with a sponge, cutting a clean pale strip through the dirt between the leaves and dusty streaks.\n\nA four-part layout then displays the cleaned areas together: a white bathtub surface, the pale tiled floor near the toilet, the white patio chair outside, and the stovetop with black burner grates. The product returns for the closing image: the purple Easy-Off BAM tub stands prominently on a white surface, with the red “NEW” graphic floating beside it. The final close-up fills the view with the label, where “Power Cleaner Easy-Off BAM Power Cleaning Crystals” is clearly visible against the bright teal, pink, and white burst design.",
